We talked about free throws, we
talked about flipping a coin,

00:08:04.170 --> 00:08:07.050
and now I'll talk about dice
because that is really another

00:08:07.050 --> 00:08:11.100
area where-- well, it's one
interesting and you'll probably

00:08:11.100 --> 00:08:14.930
see some problems
on probability.

00:08:14.930 --> 00:08:18.430
So, in general, when you're
playing games involving dice

00:08:18.430 --> 00:08:21.170
it's always interesting to say,
what's the probability if I

00:08:21.170 --> 00:08:24.470
have two six-sided dice, what's
my probability of getting--

00:08:24.470 --> 00:08:26.040
I don't know-- a
particular number.

